  "title": "Cybersecurity Engineer (Associate / Engineer / Senior)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Facilitate clear and timely communication among all stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Liaise with customers and vendors to resolve technical issues</p></li><li><p>Review customers’ business workflows or system functionalities and provide improvement recommendations</p></li><li><p>Ensure system availability with 24/7 operational support</p></li><li><p>Perform ad hoc troubleshooting and fault isolation on cybersecurity-related issues</p></li><li><p>Execute scheduled system preventive maintenance to optimize performance</p></li><li><p>Manage service requests and incidents to ensure timely and effective resolution</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with service providers and vendors to ensure SLAs are met</p></li><li><p>Provide support during critical events on a rotational basis<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements / Skills</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in IT, Computer Science, Engineering, or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Professional certifications in cybersecurity solutions preferred</p></li><li>Minimum 2 years of relevant experience preferred; fresh graduates are welcome to apply<br /></li><li>Experience in operations support</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>Windows</strong> and/or <strong>Linux</strong> operating systems</li><li>Hands-on experience with cybersecurity products such as <strong>McAfee, Cisco, Microsoft, Thales</strong></li><li>Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail</li><li>Excellent communication skills and ability to work collaboratively</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Work Location: </strong>Tampines<br /></p><p></p><p>(EA Reg No: 20C0312)</p><p>Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>kayla@talentsis.com.sg</strong> for immediate processing.</p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
